If you have a regular XP log with the same charicter (after all we are trying to keep varialbes to a minimum) showing similar DPR rates, then we can accept that perhaps there is no LvL check. But good systematic exploration of the system requires that we check our assumptions. <br>
<br>
And no I did not really think that DPR fired on misses only but Einstien wrote down a variable he later did not like and tried to erase...and modern QM still can't prove it does not belong there (the energy denisity of vaccume). Just because it is a silly idea does not mean we shoudl not take the time to disproove it.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=remfdatroll>Remf da Troll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 209<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/17/02 4:16:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1767.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: DPR</span><hr size=1> Heyas-<br>
<br>
I've always thought/assumed that DPR was separate from hits/miss calculations, primarily because it would have been pretty obvious if it wasn't, for the reasons mentioned above...  i.e. you'd get VERY few DPRs vs low level mobs (that miss most of the time), while it would work &quot;normally&quot; vs. high level ones (that hit a lot).  Haven't seen any indications that's the case, which is why I ordered the melee sequence checks the way I did before... speaking of which, worked just a bit on the list, some peer review and sanity checking please? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
format: Test;Pass result;Fail result<br>
+ = good confidence in sequence location, - = untested/unknown<br>
<br>
*attack initiated*<br>
+check if standing; continue; msg, button doesn't grey.<br>
+check for correct facing; continue; msg + restart<br>
+check for melee range; continue; msg + restart<br>
(Tested: test was to target mob and hit autoattack; when not in view, got &quot;cannot see&quot; msg, when in view but out of range got &quot;cannot hit&quot; msg.<br>
<br>
-check for innate ability proc;apply proc effect + continue; continue<br>
-check for weapon proc;apply proc effect + continue; continue<br>
(Proposed tests: check for sequence in existing logs, if proc preceeds or follows crits/ripostes/etc.).<br>
<br>
-check for riposte; msg + attack + restart; continue<br>
-check for block; msg + restart; continue<br>
-check for parry; msg + restart; continue<br>
-check for dodge; msg + restart; continue<br>
<br>
+check if weapon can hit (magic/nonmagic,immunity?); continue;msg + restart<br>
(Tested: you can get crits, weapon procs, etc. on, and riposted by, &quot;immune&quot; mobs despite not being able to &quot;hit&quot; them)<br>
<br>
-check for +/- damage shield on target; msg + apply damage; continue<br>
(Proposed test: charm ghoul, put damage shield on it, and attack it with non-magic weapons)<br>
<br>
-check for +/- innate effect on attacker; msg + apply damage; continue<br>
(Proposed test: same charmed ghoul, attacked with non-magic weapons + MoR on attacker).<br>
<br>
-determine if swing hits; continue; msg + restart<br>
-determine damage done to target<br>
*end of loop*<br>
<br>
